        <mxCell id="5rmcUgci5nsgmCFBUyWv-2" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;direction: rtl;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); background-color: transparent; font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;DATA_2BYT &amp;lt;=&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); background-color: transparent; font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); background-color: transparent; font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;{DIN, DATA_2BYT[15:8]}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;direction: rtl;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;DATA_OUT&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;=&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;{DIN, DATA_2BYT[15:8]}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;direction: rtl;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;ACTIVE_FRAME&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;=&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;ACTIVE_FRAME&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;LINE_CNT&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;lt;=&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 8px; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;LINE_CNT&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;PIXEL_CNT &amp;lt;=&amp;nbsp; PIXEL_CNT +1&lt;/font&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px; white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 8px; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-size: 12px; direction: rtl;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;If&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;LINE_CNT&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;&amp;gt; =120 and&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;LINE_CNT&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;=359&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-size: 12px; direction: rtl;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;if (PIXEL_CNT = 160) and (LINE_CNT = 120)&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-size: 12px; direction: rtl;&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-size: 12px; direction: rtl;&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-size: 12px; direction: rtl;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;ADD &amp;lt;= 0&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-size: 12px; direction: rtl;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;WEA &amp;lt;= ACTIVE&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-size: 12px; direction: rtl;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp; elseif PIXEL_CNT &amp;gt; 160 and PIXEL_CNT &amp;lt;= 479&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-size: 12px; direction: rtl;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;ADD &amp;lt;= ADD +1&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-size: 12px; direction: rtl;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;WEA &amp;lt;= ACTIVE&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 8px; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-size: 12px; direction: rtl;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;else&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-size: 12px; direction: rtl;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;ADD &amp;lt;= ADD&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-size: 12px; direction: rtl;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; WEA &amp;lt;= Not active&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;else&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-size: 12px; direction: rtl;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;ADD &amp;lt;= ADD&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-size: 12px; direction: rtl;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; WEA &amp;lt;= Not active&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 8px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="1275" y="850" width="370" height="294" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="5rmcUgci5nsgmCFBUyWv-4" value="&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Support resolution of&amp;nbsp; VGA format 480x640&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="385" width="280" height="80" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="5rmcUgci5nsgmCFBUyWv-5" value="&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Support resolution of&amp;nbsp; 240x320&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="1130" width="280" height="80" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="5rmcUgci5nsgmCFBUyWv-6" value="&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;In both SM we expected to get frame of data by 640x480. But one of the problem we incountered was the restriction of memory in our FPGA. Our FPGA dont support the amount of this data so we decide to cut pertial of the pixels. In right diagram we can see the solution for this problem&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="640" y="71" width="340" height="130" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="aKQXrO1MvT6V_a7TRgZ9-1" value="&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Under the implement above the memory in ADD = 0&amp;nbsp; will keep the 161 pixel and not 160 and so on.. but this is not really matter.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="860" y="980" width="340" height="130" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
  <diagram id="YXeu1xSn1uWGB_EFE3H_" name="Double Buffer">
    <mxGraphModel dx="2305" dy="1243" grid="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="850" pageHeight="1100" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="0" />
        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />
        <mxCell id="xKNUDe17Ow7OQQ4564UX-3" value="&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;We will generate double buffer&amp;nbsp; block to implemnt the Add for read and Add for write operations:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;1. Every time the camera finish to write a frame we need to change the writing gap.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;2. Every two times the VGA finish to read a frame (Actually its when h_count = 0 and v_count = 0) we need to change the reading gap&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;NOTE: Be aware for racing between the camera write operation and the VGA read operation. There is possibilty after a lof of frames that the VGA indicator will shift not as require because we read twice the memory 640 x 480 x 2 at 25MHz clock(while the camera write actually in 12.5MHz clock) but we have more clock for the portch area so maybe after some frames when the camera will finish to write two frame, the VGA actually will not finish to read two frame. Maybe it is ok but we need to be aware to this issue when we will write the RTL code and do some simulations.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;3. The address of GAP 2 start from 640 x480 = 307,200&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="20" y="20" width="480" height="250" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="xKNUDe17Ow7OQQ4564UX-4" value="" style="swimlane;startSize=0;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="170" y="320" width="200" height="200" as="geometry">
            <mxRectangle x="170" y="210" width="50" height="40" as="alternateBounds" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="xKNUDe17Ow7OQQ4564UX-5" value="" style="endArrow=none;html=1;rounded=0;curved=1;exitX=1;exitY=0.3;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;exitPerimeter=0;entryX=0;entryY=0.5;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" parent="xKNUDe17Ow7OQQ4564UX-4" target="xKNUDe17Ow7OQQ4564UX-4" edge="1">
          <mxGeometry width="50" height="50" relative="1" as="geometry">
            <mxPoint x="200" y="99" as="sourcePoint" />
            <mxPoint x="140" y="99" as="targetPoint" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="xKNUDe17Ow7OQQ4564UX-6" value="GAP 1&lt;br&gt;640 x 480" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" parent="xKNUDe17Ow7OQQ4564UX-4" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="70" y="40" width="60" height="30" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="xKNUDe17Ow7OQQ4564UX-10" value="GAP 2&lt;br&gt;640 x 480" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" parent="xKNUDe17Ow7OQQ4564UX-4" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="70" y="130" width="60" height="30" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
  <diagram id="F5i3nxWTW5J4RvjO4D1g" name="VGA">
    <mxGraphModel dx="1098" dy="592" grid="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="850" pageHeight="1100" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="0" />
        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />
        <mxCell id="-u5jGCXjM1uGniPdbxkn-1" value="&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(10, 10, 10); font-family: &amp;quot;Google Sans&amp;quot;, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;VGA protocol:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(10, 10, 10); font-family: &amp;quot;Google Sans&amp;quot;, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;VGA 640x480 @ 60Hz (for refresg frame). How we get 60Hz as require?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(10, 10, 10); font-family: &amp;quot;Google Sans&amp;quot;, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;The protcol demand for horizontal timing: 640 Visible video pixels + 16 Fron porch + 96 HSYNC pulse + 48 Back portch = In total 800 clocks.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#0a0a0a&quot; face=&quot;Google Sans, Arial, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;For vertical timing the protocol demand: 480 Visible rows + 10 Front portch + 2 VSYNC pulse + 33 Back portch = In total 525.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#0a0a0a&quot; face=&quot;Google Sans, Arial, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#0a0a0a&quot; face=&quot;Google Sans, Arial, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;The vertical timing increment every 800 clock. Thus the total clocks we need for one frame is 800 x 525 = 420,000 pixels clocks per frame.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#0a0a0a&quot; face=&quot;Google Sans, Arial, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#0a0a0a&quot; face=&quot;Google Sans, Arial, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;25M ; 25,000,000 / 420,000 = 59.52Hz, aproximitaly 60Hz/&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#0a0a0a&quot; face=&quot;Google Sans, Arial, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;So this is how we support 60Hz&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="20" y="18" width="230" height="320" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="LaHu4vveBmDz8ez77Lnc-1" value="" style="shape=image;verticalLabelPosition=bottom;labelBackgroundColor=default;verticalAlign=top;aspect=fixed;imageAspect=0;image=data:image/png,;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="20" y="340" width="220" height="126.86" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="1HHIAuu24n-46XRj9xOQ-1" value="" style="shape=image;verticalLabelPosition=bottom;labelBackgroundColor=default;verticalAlign=top;aspect=fixed;imageAspect=0;image=data:image/png,;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="20" y="490" width="220" height="145.93" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="1Gokxyi5CJYR6zeoFC4V-1" value="&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Principles for VGA design block:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;1. We need create continous data flow to the screen if not, the screen will unlock. We will generate continous signal HSYNC and VSYNC by two diffrient coutner, h_count and v_count. The signal define as we can see at the pictures in the left side.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;We always need to create those signal without any condition, so there will not be any condition for those counters!&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;2.The VGA block communicate with two independent blocks. One is the screen display so we need to generate VSYNC, HSYNC, RED, GREEN, BLUE while the second block its the RAM. The VGA block need to read data from RAM and print out over the screen.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;In those parts we need to decide when to read data and when to display black pixels.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;3. To implement the read operation from the RAM we need to understand few things.&lt;br&gt;As we saw already the OV7670 need two PCLK(25M) cycles to read one pixel when we choose one of the RGB modes. We will write data to memory every two clocks so the data flow actually at 12.5MHz.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;from the other hand, the counters of HSYNC and VSYNC working on 25MHz (we can understand that from the calaculation we did at the left side). So the display operation finish scan two frames when the camera finish to write just one (approximatly, because h_count and v_count include back portch, front portch...). The second scan will be cleaner&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;because&lt;br&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;the camera has had more time to fill the RAM with new data.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-align: justify; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-family: Helvetica;&quot;&gt;In this case we need to understand that tearing issue will occurs. Meaning, the VGA will display some pixel from the old frame and some pixel from the new frame.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;If we dont use double buffer tearing will be for sure and we just can make the picture less sensetive by fix the tearing always at the same place. We will do it by using ready signal that said to the VGA block read data only when VSYNC of the camera go high and its ready will stay at high untill h_count and v_count will be at zero. This conditions will promise fix tearing in the start of the frame and not in random rows in the frame.&lt;b&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;en-IL&quot; style=&quot;line-height: 115%; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;By using the Ready signal&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;en-IL&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255)); text-align: left; line-height: 115%; font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;&quot;&gt; to&lt;br&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;force the VGA to start reading Address 0 only when the camera starts writing &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;address 0.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;We can skip this tearing issue by using double buffer method on the dual port ram. In this case our memory will be x2 and half of the memory belong to the old frame and half to the new frame. At procedure the camera will write the data to part a and VGA will read data from part b aftter that they will toggle so the camera will write data to part b and VGA will read data form part a.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;4. So what is the content of the VGA block? First we will create counter that for VSYNC and HSYNC. Next it&#39;s process that will decide when to read another pixel from the memory. (If we are choosing double buffer solution so the camera will not be sensetive when i move her or the object, we need to implment toggle operation in the camera side and the VGA side)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="256" y="23" width="290" height="990" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="os5D9ZvCErk9AQtNWTqe-2" value="&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Implement Block:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;In the VGA block we dont need to implement FSM.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;We just need to follow some principle:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;1. No matter if we use double buffer or not we will reset the read add from ram when ready_in = 1 and h_count = 0 and v_count = 0. The Capture block generate ready signal at high for one clock only. we will need to detect the change of this signal and create ready signal that not act as pulse. the signal will keep high untill v_count and h_count = 0 and then this signal will go low.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;(When ready_in = 1 and h_count = 0 and v_count = 0 we will reset the add)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;2. Between h_count &amp;lt; 639 and v_count &amp;lt;479 we will increment the Add signal each cycle and the GREEN, BLUE, RED signal will get the data signal from the ram. outside of this domain the Add signal will not increment and the GREEN, BLUE, RED signal will get zero (Black pixels)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;3. h_count and v_count will increment every clock cycle no matter what untill we will need to reset their value. While the Hsync and Vsync signals will define as shown in the picture on the left.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" parent="1" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry x="560" y="24" width="270" height="413" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="ERte0m_iQomiTaFshifW-1" value="The capture block work with 50MHz and the VGA block work with 25MHz.&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;clock so the VGA and the Capture blocks finish at the same time. What i wrote above correct for capture block in 25MHz.&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontStyle=1" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="270" y="1013" width="710" height="60" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
</mxfile>
